cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper describes the implementation and use of a high-level Python API for machine learning model development, which is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on developing a tool to simplify and accelerate the machine learning model development process. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the integration of custom algorithms and solutions for model construction and evaluation. cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are also possible categories as the tool can be used for image and text analysis. Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper mentions the use of established machine learning toolboxes.
